WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:05.180 --> 00:00:09.850
hi I'm Peg from Sony and I'm going to
show you how to pair your Sony Tablet S

00:00:09.850 --> 00:00:12.119
to another Bluetooth device

00:00:12.119 --> 00:00:15.399
in the upper right hand corner
of the desktop screen

00:00:15.399 --> 00:00:19.560
tap the apps icon

00:00:19.560 --> 00:00:26.560
then tap the settings icon

00:00:27.509 --> 00:00:33.440
in the setting screen select
wireless &amp; networks

00:00:33.440 --> 00:00:37.530
in the wireless &amp; networks screen make
sure that the Bluetooth function has a

00:00:37.530 --> 00:00:39.100
check mark

00:00:39.100 --> 00:00:42.400
if there is no green check next to the
Bluetooth feature

00:00:42.400 --> 00:00:44.190
it is not enabled

00:00:44.190 --> 00:00:51.190
tap Bluetooth to turn on the
Bluetooth function

00:00:51.540 --> 00:00:54.830
at this point you will need to make sure
that the Bluetooth device you were

00:00:54.830 --> 00:00:56.819
attempting to pair with the tablet

00:00:56.819 --> 00:00:59.490
is set to discoverable

00:00:59.490 --> 00:01:04.620
if the device is not set to discoverable
the tablet will not see it and will be

00:01:04.620 --> 00:01:09.260
unable to connect refer to the
instruction or user manual for that device

00:01:10.170 --> 00:01:14.600
for information on how to set the device
as discoverable

00:01:14.600 --> 00:01:17.480
in the wireless &amp; network screen

00:01:17.480 --> 00:01:22.720
tap Bluetooth settings

00:01:22.720 --> 00:01:25.110
in the Bluetooth settings screen

00:01:25.110 --> 00:01:31.980
tap find nearby devices

00:01:31.980 --> 00:01:36.810
the tablet will scan and display all
nearby Bluetooth devices that have been

00:01:36.810 --> 00:01:41.120
set as discoverable and are broadcasting

00:01:41.120 --> 00:01:43.790
in the find nearby devices screen

00:01:43.790 --> 00:01:49.090
below found devices a list of all
discovered bluetooth devices will be displayed

00:01:50.610 --> 00:01:55.180
tap the Bluetooth device you wish to
pair with

00:01:55.180 --> 00:01:57.950
in the Bluetooth pairing request prompt

00:01:57.950 --> 00:02:01.410
tap pair to confirm the connection

00:02:01.410 --> 00:02:05.240
you may be required to confirm the
connection on the Bluetooth device as well

00:02:06.380 --> 00:02:11.310
refer to the instruction or user manual
for that device for information on how

00:02:11.310 --> 00:02:13.739
to confirm a connection request

00:02:13.739 --> 00:02:17.239
the selected device is now connected
with the tablet

00:02:17.239 --> 00:02:24.239
and will be showing in the Bluetooth
settings screen under paired devices

